rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description:
An employer is an organization or person that has hired workers to perform functions.
Things that are employers:
## Corporations (e.g.: Nintendo, Skanska, SK Telecom).
## Small businesses (e.g.: GoGet CarShare Flipboard).
## Non-profit organizations (e.g.: Greenpeace, Drupal Association).
## Governments and government agencies (e.g.: Finland, KGB, United States Postal Service).
## Restaurants (e.g.: McCormick & Schmicks, Starbucks).
## Companies that are subsidiaries of larger companies (e.g.: Subaru France, Nike Skateboarding).
## Educational Institutions (e.g.: The Open University, Stockholm School of Economics, Yonsei University).
Things that are NOT employers:
## Fictional employers (e.g.: Hogwarts School of Witchcraft and Wizardry, Bluth Company). Use mso:fictional_universe.employer for these.
## Companies using freelancers or independent contractors (e.g.: McKinsey & Company, when working with Brad Greenlee). Freelancers and independent contractors have clients, not employers.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Employer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an employer to the average amount of time, in months, that a person is employed by the employer.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Average Tenure

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links an employer to information about the employee benefits offered by the employer.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Benefits

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:business.employer to the mso: that collect the data about types of employees for the given employer. Data include the number, average salary, and years experience.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Employees by Title

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Employment Tenure

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type collecting the data on a product endorsement. Data includes the product, the agent endorsing the product, and the dates of endorsement.

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:business.product_endorsement entity to the mso:business.endorsed_product.

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:business.product_endorsement to the mso:business.product_endorsee, the agent that owns the product being endorsed.

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:business.product_endorsement entity to the mso:business.product_endorser, the agent endorsing the product.

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all product ingredients. These are the substances that are combined into products.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Product Ingredient

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:business.product_ingredient to its derivative mso:business.product_ingredient(s).
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Derivatives

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:business.product_ingredient to a mso:business.product_ingredient the former derived from.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Derived from

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Use this property with compound ingredients -- those ingredients that are listed as containing other ingredients, as in \"cheddar cheese (milk, salt, cheese cultures)\". Each sub-ingredient can be listed here.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ingredients

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Ingredients that this is a variety, or kind, of. For example, 'rolled oats' is a variety of 'oats', 'organic lavender oil' is a variety of 'lavender oil'.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Variety of

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all product lines. These are the sets of loosely related products offered for individual sale.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Product Line

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The brand that this product line is marketed under.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Brand

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:business.product_line to its mso:business.product_category, e.g., shampoos, dolls, cellular phones.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Category

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The company that is responsible for this product line.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Producer(s)

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:business.product_line to its mso:commerce.consumer_product(s).
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Products

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:business.product_line to the date the line was introduced.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Introduced

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:business.product_line to its mso:business.product_theme(s).
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Themes

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all product themes. These are the broad means of classifying 'aboutness' of a product. For example, a re-release of a Frank Sinatra Christmas album may have a theme of 'Frank Sinatra' and 'Holiday' or 'Christmas'.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Product Theme

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:business.product_theme to the mso:commerce.consumer_product(s) with this theme.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Products

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:business.product_theme to the mso:business.product_line(s) that have this theme. A product line is a collection of consumer products, produced by the same company, that are related in some way.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Product Lines

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all products with ingredients. These are the drug, beauty, and food products that contain constituent components to create a unit. A product may contain only one ingredient, for example, a cosmetic may be 100% witch hazel.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Product with Ingredients

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:business.product_with_ingredients to its mso:business.product_ingredient(s)
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ingredient

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A business or individual that provides document storage and management solutions. Includes companies that specialize in the safe destruction/disposal of records, as well as companies that specialize in media storage for preservation purposes (e.g., celluloid film storage/management).
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Records Management

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A business operation that installs and maintains automated machines that permit customers to rent items, e.g. DVDs, bikes, and luggage carts.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Rental Kiosk Company

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A business or individual that provides research services, such as report writing, information retrieval, and clipping services.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Research Service

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Any business operation that sells products directly to consumers.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Retailer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A URL pointing to a catalog of the products offered by the given retailer.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Digital Catalog

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that links a retailer to a product offer of the retailer.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Offer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a retailer to a form of payment that is accepted by the retailer.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Payment Method

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A business that specializes in the manufacture and/or distribution and products that are made out of rubber and/or plastic.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Rubber and Plastics Company

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A business that specializes in the manufacturing, distribution, and/or wholesaling of scientific equipment, including laboratory equipment, to businesses, government agencies, or organizations.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Scientific Equipment Company

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A business or individual that offers secretarial services to corporations and businesses. Includes executive secretarial services, remote secretarial services, off-site secretarial services, legal secretarial services, and so on.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Secretarial Service

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all shareholders. These are the agents that own shares in companies.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Shareholder

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:business.shareholder to the mso:business.holding(s) the shareholder has or had.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Holding

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An individual or business that specializes in packing and/or sending items to another location. Note that this type does not include government post offices.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Shipping Service

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A complex consisting of retail stores with walkways connecting the stores.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Shopping Center

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:business.shopping_center_owner to the mso:business.shopping_center(s) the agents own.

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:business.sponsorship entity to the mso:business.sponsor.

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:business.sponsorship entity to the agent that is sponsored, mso:business.sponsored_recipient.

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Value type representing an entry in the Standard Industrial Classification (SIC). This is a system used by government agencies to classify industry areas. While the SIC code is being deprecated by the NAICS code, see mso:business.industry.naics_2007, there are still agencies that use the SIC code, like the US Securities and Exchange Commission. Properties for this value type include the numerical code, code description (please use object.type.description), and year the code is in effect.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Standard Industrial Classification (SIC)

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a Standard Industrial Classification (SIC) value type to the numerical portion of the code. For example, an entry in the 2007 SIC code includes "01120 - Growing of rice". This property would be used to relate the "01120" portion of the entry to the full entry.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Numerical SIC code

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an entry in the Standard Industrial Classification (SIC) to the year of the classification version. For example, an entry in the 2007 SIC code includes "01120 - Growing of rice". This property would be used to relate the year "2007" to the entry.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type collecting the data on stock ticker symbols, including the symbol and the exchange on which the stock is listed.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Stock Ticker Symbol

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:business.stock_ticker_symbol to the mso:business.issue for the symbol.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Issue

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:business.stock_ticker_symbol to the mso:finance.stock_exchange for this symbol.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Stock Exchange

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:business.stock_ticker_symbol to the text of the symbol.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ticker Symbol

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An individual or business that specializes in the rental and/or sale of large-scale storage units, whether buildings, parts of buildings or containers (e.g., cargo containers).
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Storage Service

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A retailer that occupies a showroom where customers can visit and make purchases.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Storefront Retailer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Open-air markets where items, whether new or used, are sold by a variety of vendors.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Street Market

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An company that provides voice or data transmission services, such as AT&T, Verizon and Qwest.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Telecommunication Company

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Retail establishments that sell donated items to provide funds for a charitable organization.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Thrift Store

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Stores that sell products made from tobacco, e.g. cigars and cigarettes, loose tobacco, and products for using tobacco, e.g. pipes.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Tobacco Shop

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all trade unions. Trade unions are the organizations that are formed to bargain with employers.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Trade Union

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:business.trade_union to the mso:business.industry(ies) the union is associated with.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Industry

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:business.trade_union to the mso:people.profession(s) the union represents.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Professions represented

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An individual or business that specializes in converting live or recorded speech into a written or electronic document for commercial or legal purposes. Includes court reporters and court reporting services.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Transcription Service

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An individual or business that specializes in translating oral or written communications from one language to another. Includes sign language interpretation.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Translation Service

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A large retailer that sells wholesale quantities of food and other products to both individuals and small businesses that are members of the store.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Warehouse Club Store

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all wholesale stores. These are the locations for wholesale, which are the sales of goods to merchants.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Wholesale Store

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A business that specializes in services related to logging, wood milling, paper milling, and the manufacturing of wood and paper products.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Woodworking Company
